{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3504936,"name":"Harrison","username":"hjmcphail76","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/hjmcphail76/{size}/234713_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-07T13:16:36.515Z","cooked":"<p>Hi all.</p>
<p>We are using 2 neos with 25:1 max planetarys for our elevator this year. I would like some help on how to tune the <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> for it, I already have it configured and running to setpoints, but since it is under gravity  and it is not tuned well the <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> causes the motors to vibrate around their setpoint. (Unfortunately I don’t have a video)</p>
<p>I have tried looking through the Rev starter bot code since they implemented a similar system and it seems to work fine?</p>
<p>I do want to put out there that I am essentially our only trained programmer that also does 90 percent of CAD… while I could go with <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> on rio and do feedforward and SYSID I would rather keep this simple and allow me to put my efforts towards my automated scoring/pickup routines/dashboard I made.</p>
<p>Here is the code:</p>
